**CLASSIFICATION HINTS:**

MRI Sequences:
- T1-weighted: CSF dark, fat bright, good anatomical detail
- T2-weighted: CSF bright, fluid-sensitive
- FLAIR: CSF suppressed (dark), lesions remain bright
- DWI: Diffusion-weighted, restricted diffusion appears bright
- SWI/GRE: Susceptibility-weighted, blood products appear dark
- Post-contrast T1: Enhancement of pathology

CT:
- Non-contrast: Bone bright, CSF dark
- Contrast-enhanced: Vessels and enhancing lesions bright
- CT angiography: Arterial phase with vessel opacification
